<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56b70572-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2107"><num value="2107">§ 2107.</num><heading> Selection boards; composition of boards</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A board convened under <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s2106">section 2106 of this title</ref> shall consist of five or more officers on the active duty promotion list who are serving in or above the grade to which the board may recommend officers for promotion. No officer may be a member of two successive boards convened to consider officers of the same grade for promotion.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56b70573-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/88/130/s1/10/C">Pub. L. 88–130, § 1(10)(C)</ref>, <date date="1963-09-24">Sept. 24, 1963</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/77/179">77 Stat. 179</ref>, § 252; renumbered § 2107 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI">Pub. L. 115–282, title I</ref>, §§ 112(b), 123(b)(2), <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4216">132 Stat. 4216</ref>, 4240.)</sourceCredit>
